### When reaching out to me, my preferences are:
- Send me an email
- Send me a 1:1 message in Slack or Discord or Linkedin etc.
- Tag me in a merge request
- Tag me in an `issue` or in `epic` or in any other `work_item`

# What does my typical working day look like?

I'm in [EET, UTC+2 or EEST, UTC+3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_European_Time) and here are some details:
- 8am - waking up, have a breakfast, walk through social media, sloowly heading out to the office space nearby.
- 9am - starting work-related activities: coffee, emails, chats, charts, etc.
- 1pm or so - lunch and loong walk. Maybe some out-of-work appointments. ~Maybe a gym.~
- 4pm or so - return to work-related activities.
- 8pm - wrap up my day, switching into nonworking mode: coffee, chats, art, volunteering. Heading out from the office space with no connection unless production incident.

~_A note #1: I tend to practice late stays and over-the-weekend learning activities. It may look a bit unhealthy... but it is definitely not for my current life stage üòá. Work enviroment is the safest place I have..._~

~_A note #2: I tend to be overexcited on some mornings and propose crazy things in slack or elsewhere. Bear with me or make a short DM with your thoughts. Simple YES/NO questions are the most valuable_~

_A note #0: I'm working on establishing better #workwarbalance habits atm. Check my progress on the [board](https://gitlab.com/petrokoriakin1/petrokoriakin1/-/boards/5432145)_


